# postgres cheatsheet


## IMPORTANT: https://dba.stackexchange.com/questions/43920/why-does-pg-lsclusters-not-list-my-postgres-cluster
### Use postgres common tools consistently, as they are just wrappers 

initdb -D (directory_for_db) => initialize database cluster more on: https://www.postgresql.org/docs/9.5/static/creating-cluster.html
postgres -D (dircetory_for_db) => starts database server options for pointing to different conf files on: (https://stackoverflow.com/questions/37861262/create-multiple-postgres-instances-on-same-machine)

